<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-05T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-05T10:00:00-05:00" n="512" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d512">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2231/184: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gonzalez</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-05T11:00:00-04:00">August 5, 1937—11
                                a.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>29. Legation’s 43, August 3, noon. You are authorized to present Schedule
                            I of proposed trade agreement to the Minister for Foreign Affairs after
                            making the following changes therein: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p rend="flushleft">Tariff item No. 13–a; hog lard; duty, G. K.,
                                    Sucres 0.25; No. 87, wheat flour; duty, G. K. 0.075. Tariff
                                    items 688 and 703, tubes and tires; duty, L. K. Sucres 1.40.</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>Department assumes you have made substitution of tariff items 647, 740
                            and 1079–n in accordance with instruction No. 249, July 28.<note n="41" xml:id="d512fn41">Not printed.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>